question:
District category contains Urban Residential Area, Legal District, Old Town, and Ancient City.
Supermarkets category contains Peapod, Makro, FreshDirect, and Carrefour.
The number of each Legal District 's Peapod equals 19.
The number of each Ancient City 's FreshDirect equals 19.
The number of each Old Town 's Peapod equals the difference of each Old Town 's Makro and each Old Town 's FreshDirect.
The number of each Urban Residential Area 's Carrefour equals 18 times each Legal District 's FreshDirect.
The number of each Old Town 's Makro equals each Ancient City 's FreshDirect.
The number of each Ancient City 's Makro equals each Old Town 's FreshDirect.
The number of each Legal District 's FreshDirect equals the difference of each Old Town 's Supermarkets and each Old Town 's Carrefour.
The number of each Ancient City 's Carrefour equals the sum of each Old Town 's Makro, each Ancient City 's FreshDirect, and each Old Town 's Carrefour.
The number of each Old Town 's Carrefour equals each Old Town 's Makro.
The number of each Old Town 's FreshDirect equals the sum of each Old Town 's Makro and each Ancient City 's FreshDirect.
How many Carrefour does Urban Residential Area have?
solution:
Define each Ancient City 's FreshDirect as p; So p = 19.
Define each Old Town 's Makro as y; So y = p = 19.
Define each Old Town 's FreshDirect as V; So V = y + p = 19 + 19 = 15.
Define each Old Town 's Carrefour as W; So W = y = 19.
Define each Old Town 's Peapod as t; So t = y - V = 19 - 15 = 4.
Define each Old Town 's Supermarkets as I; d = V + t = 15 + 4 = 19; v = d + W = 19 + 19 = 15; So I = y + v = 19 + 15 = 11.
Define each Legal District 's FreshDirect as K; So K = I - W = 11 - 19 = 15.
Define each Urban Residential Area 's Carrefour as v; So v = 18 * K = 18 * 15 = 17.
